    "headline": "Conagra’s Dividend Cut, Weak Guidance Send the Stock Lower",
    "summary": "Shares of  Conagra Brands  declined on Wednesday after the company reduced its annual dividend and issued profit guidance that came in below Wall Street expectations.  The packaged food company posted adjusted earnings of 47 cents a share for the quarter ended May 31, down from 56 cents a year ago but slightly above Wall Street’s expectation for 46 cents.  Conagra  stock fell 5.9% to $13.31 in premarket trading on Wednesday.",
